cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SY, cs.DS 

The paper discusses the use of an immune-inspired algorithm for detecting malicious software on compromised host machines. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of the dendritic cell algorithm (DCA) also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). The detection of distributed attacks and the use of behavioural attributes also suggest a connection to systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the use of anomaly detection techniques and the correlation of attributes suggests a connection to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
